## Key Results

- **Line Spectrum Confirmed**: DJIA exhibits discrete spectral peaks, not continuous noise
- **Nominal Line Spacing**: 0.3676 rad/yr confirmed across 130 years, 2 markets (std=0.0015)
- **79 Individual Harmonics Resolved**: Narrowband CMW confirms N=2-80 in daily DJIA (R²=0.9999)
- **Amplitude-Frequency Law**: a(w) = k/w confirmed (all cycles have equal max rate of change)
- **Reconstruction**: 6-filter decomposition captures 96.2% of signal energy
- **Trading Methodology**: Walk-forward Sharpe 2.10 (DJIA), 1.69 (SPX) — 3.8× buy-and-hold
- **Critical Finding**: F4→F2 leading and F3/F6 trough amplification are Hurst-era artifacts that reverse on modern data. Synchronicity scoring, amplitude regime, and asymmetry are the stable strategies.

